<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">You read that right. WhatsApp is <a href="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/smartphones/642264-whatsapp-testing-paid-subscription.html" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">testing paid subscriptions</a> that unlock features like more pinned chats, custom app icons, themed interfaces, and exclusive ringtones and stickers. Fun, but we&#8217;ll see how that plays out.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">South Africa&rsquo;s communication regulator, the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA), is also side-eyeing the platform and other over-the-top (OTT) services like Netflix. The focus is to <a href="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/broadcasting/642343-plan-to-investigate-netflix-and-whatsapp-in-south-africa.html" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">open a market inquiry</a> into whether these services are eating into the space that traditional broadcasters once dominated, and what that means for competition and regulation. Findings are expected after the 2026/2027 financial year.</p>
